text: The name Josephine [ joh-zuh-feen, -suh- ] is a female given name. Josephine is a timeless name that has been well-liked for hundreds of years. It is the feminine version of the name Joseph and has a meaning of "God will increase" or "may Jehovah add/give increase." There are many variants. The name is a female version of Joseph (which is a Hebrew version of Yosef). There are many celebrities with the name Josephine and related forms, although the name is only marginally popular in the United States. == People == * Josephine Baker, American-born French dancer, singer and actress (1906â€“1975) * Josephine Butlerm, British feminist and social reformer fighting to end child prostitution * Josephine Hull, American stage and film actress (1877-1957) ==References== Category:Given names
